EQUINE INFECTIOUS ANEMIA - GERMANY (03): (HAMBURG, BAVARIA) SPREAD
******************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

In this post:
[1] A new case of EIA, Hamburg
[2] 5 new EIA cases, Bavaria

******
[1] A new case of EIA, Hamburg
Date: Mon 26 Jun 2017
Source: Pferderevue [in German, trans. submitter SZ, edited]
https://tinyurl.com/y9ky8wm3


After [Fri 23 Jun 2017] confirmation of a 3rd case of EIA [equine infectious anemia] there is now suspicion of an additional case.

A holding in Hamburg-Osdorf is affected, according to the Health and Consumer Protection Authority information upon request of 'Pferderevue' on [Mon 25 Jun 2017]. A horse stabled at the premise was tested by a private laboratory for equine infectious anemia. The official test result by the Friedrich-Loeffler-Institut is still pending.

As a precautionary measure, protective measures have already been taken, and blood samples have been obtained from the other horses of the holding. The results are expected at the end of the week.

Yet, it has not been established whether the cases from Hagen-Grinden, Düsseldorf-Kalkum, Bad Bentheim and now Hamburg-Osdorf are connected. The epidemiological investigations of the positive samples showed that the horse from the district of Verden had previously participated in an official polo tournament in Bad Bentheim. Further connections are under investigation.

